001package org.biopax.paxtools.impl.level3;
002
003import org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.DnaRegionReference;
004import org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.DnaRegion;
005import org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.EntityReference;
006import org.biopax.paxtools.util.IllegalBioPAXArgumentException;
007
008
009public class DnaRegionImpl extends NucleicAcidImpl implements DnaRegion
010{
011        public DnaRegionImpl() {
012        }
013        
014// ------------------------ INTERFACE METHODS ------------------------
015
016        @Override
017        public void setEntityReference(EntityReference entityReference) {
018                if(entityReference instanceof DnaRegionReference || entityReference == null)
019                        super.setEntityReference(entityReference);
020                else
021                        throw new IllegalBioPAXArgumentException("setEntityReference failed: "
022                                        + entityReference.getUri() + " is not a DnaRegionReference.");
023        }
024
025
026// --------------------- Interface BioPAXElement ---------------------
027
028    @Override
029        public Class<? extends DnaRegion> getModelInterface()
030        {
031                return DnaRegion.class;
032        }
033
034}
